│ in this sinking logic. The algorithm for finding an optimal insertion point decides to     │
│ sink an `insertelement` instruction that is an intermediate part of building a vector      │
│ operand for the vectorizer itself. The sinking logic incorrectly analyzes the              │
│ instruction's uses, failing to account for the new `shufflevector` use that is being       │
│ created in a different (and dominating) block. This results in the `insertelement` being   │
│ placed in a block that is dominated by its user, leading to the verifier error.\n\n### 4.  │
